# zoo_0000 main loop - no title screen, no hero: boots directly into
# xlector control of the zoo, per the standard's own core idea (see
# dox/xlector-standard.md) - a game following this pattern does NOT
# need a "player" piece to exist by default. x1/x2 are the same
# history-read-cursor/last-key registers every project in this family
# uses (mutaclsym/egg-pals/1.TPMOS all share this shape).
# x9 = 113 ('q'), the same fixed, non-numbered quit key convention
# every sibling project uses - never routed through the numbered
# accumulator.
li x1, 0
li x9, 113

compose_frame
compose_rgb_frame
hit_frame

loop:
read_history x2, x1
beq x2, x0, no_key
beq x2, x9, quit
xlector_input x2
tick_pets
compose_frame
compose_rgb_frame
hit_frame
no_key:
sleep 30000
j loop

quit:
halt
